cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of inferring the topology of a network using network coding. It involves the use of algorithms and techniques related to network information theory (cs.IT), network science (cs.SI), and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the algorithms through simulations, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and security and cryptography (cs.CR) to compare them with other techniques.
